<section class="alchemy-section">
  <div class="container">

    <h2>What this is</h2>
    <p>
      Most change efforts fail because they stay at the surface: tools, strategy, behavior tips.
      Alchemy works deeper — at the level of meaning-making and survival patterns.
      That’s where the loop actually lives.
    </p>

    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Facilitated</h3>
        <p>
          A trained facilitator guides the session so it stays out of blame and inside observation.
          The goal is clarity, not performance.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Experiential</h3>
        <p>
          Participants work with a set of structured prompts (“cards”) that surface real patterns quickly —
          without forcing personal disclosure.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Practical</h3>
        <p>
          Every session ends with a small, testable shift — language, boundary, or practice —
          that teams can apply immediately.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


<section class="alchemy-section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>What it helps with</h2>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Pressure & performance loops</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Over-functioning and burnout cycles</li>
          <li>Perfectionism, urgency, and reactivity</li>
          <li>Low psychological safety under deadlines</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Communication & conflict</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Defensiveness, avoidance, and blame</li>
          <li>Unspoken expectations and role confusion</li>
          <li>Repair conversations after friction</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Change & adoption</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Resistance that looks like “noncompliance”</li>
          <li>Stalled initiatives and circular meetings</li>
          <li>Building flexible, adaptive teams</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Team cohesion</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Trust-building without forced vulnerability</li>
          <li>Better boundaries and cleaner collaboration</li>
          <li>Shared language for patterns</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


<section class="alchemy-section">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>How a session works</h2>

    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">1</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Orientation</h3>
          <p>We set a simple container: observe patterns, avoid blame, stay present, stay honest.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">2</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Pattern selection</h3>
          <p>Participants choose prompts that match what’s happening right now (no randomness required).</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">3</div>
        <div>
          <h3>Facilitated reflection</h3>
          <p>We name the loop: what triggers it, what it protects, and what it costs the team.</p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="step">
        <div class="num">4</div>
        <div>
          <h3>One practical shift</h3>
          <p>We choose one small action that changes the loop: a phrase, a boundary, a meeting rule, a practice.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="callout">
      <strong>Holding question (mid-session):</strong>
      <span>“What is this pattern trying to protect — and what is it costing us?”</span>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>


<section class="alchemy-section alt">
  <div class="container">
    <h2>Formats</h2>

    <div class="grid-3">
      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Single Session</h3>
        <p>Best for teams that need clarity fast: pressure, conflict, or decision bottlenecks.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h3>3-Session Arc</h3>
        <p>A short series where teams practice new responses and stabilize a new pattern.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="panel">
        <h3>Facilitator Training</h3>
        <p>Train internal leaders to run sessions with integrity and keep work in second-order space.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <p class="note">
      Sessions can be in-person (Bali / travel) or online. Team size is flexible.
    </p>

  </div>
</section>


